OL,6,F"There is nothing that I can say or do
OL,7,Fthat will fill the void in the lives
OL,8,Fof the family and friends of Grace
OL,9,FFoulds and Marie Cunningham. I can
OL,10,Fonly hope that everyone affected by
OL,11,Fthis case will understand that my task
OL,12,Fis to impose a sentence in accordance
OL,13,Fwith the law.J"The sole cause of their
OL,14,Fdeaths was your dangerous driving. The
OL,15,Freason you hit them is because you
OL,16,Fsimply did not see them.J"That much is
OL,17,Fclear from the fact that you did not
OL,18,Fbrake. The reason you did not see them
OL,19,Fis equally clear."There is some
OL,20,Fevidence that, after the collision,
OL,21,Fyou drove over the body of Marie
OL,22,FCunningham. Even if you did, I am
OL,23,Fsatisfied that it was not a deliberate
OL,24,Fact done in an attempt to avoid the
OL,25,Fconsequences of your actions.J"The
OL,26,Freason you did not see Grace Foulds
